<item>
            <title>[LU-3043] server build for sles11sp2 is broken</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3043</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While building with the latest recipe for sles11sp2 server from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1812&quot; title=&quot;3.6/FC18 Server Patches&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1812&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1812&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I discovered a new build failure.  Errors look like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;  CC [M]  /home/bogl/lustre-release/lustre/mdt/mdt_handler.o
cc1: warnings being treated as errors
/home/bogl/lustre-release/lustre/mdt/mdt_handler.c: In function &#8216;mdt_path_current&#8217;:
/home/bogl/lustre-release/lustre/mdt/mdt_handler.c:5550: error: &#8216;rc&#8217; may be used uninitialized in this function
make[6]: *** [/home/bogl/lustre-release/lustre/mdt/mdt_handler.o] Error 1
make[5]: *** [/home/bogl/lustre-release/lustre/mdt] Error 2
make[4]: *** [/home/bogl/lustre-release/lustre] Error 2
make[3]: *** [_module_/home/bogl/lustre-release] Error 2
make[3]: Leaving directory `/home/bogl/linux-3.0.58-0.6.6&apos;
make[2]: *** [modules] Error 2
make[2]: Leaving directory `/home/bogl/lustre-release&apos;
make[1]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1
make[1]: Leaving directory `/home/bogl/lustre-release&apos;
make: *** [all] Error 2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe this failure came from code added in recent commit a19f706ebef23a5778572553256df78abb81e1a4, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2801&quot; title=&quot;Checking remote object by wrong way(mdt_object_exists) in mdt_swap_layouts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2801&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2801&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; mdt: checking remote object in mdt_swap_layouts.  It isn&apos;t an issue in normal lustre builds in Centos.  It hasn&apos;t been seen in routine lustre builds for sles11sp2 since those are currently client only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will push a trivial patch for this soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
